            "answer_text": "No, they\u2019re much better than people give them credit for. I think the author did some really cool things to add to the Vampire lore like the Volturi and the fact that it takes three days of burning to basically turn into stone. What critics constantly forget is that this is, at the end of the day, a YA series. I found it enjoyable and most of the people who hate it, I\u2019ve discovered, haven\u2019t actually read it. They\u2019ve only seen memes and base their judgement on that (oy.) Bella is misunderstood because she doesn\u2019t represent masculine strengths. She\u2019s got what have long been seen as feminine strengths. She protects rather than attack but she\u2019s far from the passive wimp she\u2019s accused of being. It is kind of disturbing that we only value masculine violence (Katniss from Hunger Games anyone?) and we devalue anything else. Just read them for yourself and don\u2019t let other people stop you from an enjoyable experience. Check out Victoria Nelson\u2019s lecture on the mythology behind the novels in a youtube called \u201cStephanie Meyer and the 21st Century Vampire Romance\u201d from Claremont University. ",
